<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCCE53F53CB81A16701F975" box="[1006,1034,1705,1729]" captionStart="Figs 42–54" captionStartId="46.[189,229,2012,2034]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,232,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-109@46.[189,1436,232,1971]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figs 42–54: Forebody of Zyras spp.: kraatzi (42), exasperatus (43), pindarae (44), perforatus (45), championi (46), pallipes (47), condignus, holotype (48), condignus, Nepal (49), nigroaeneus (50), morvani (51), truncatus (52), longilobatus (53), hastatus (54). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742371/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">46</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCCE53F543C81A1673DF975" box="[1049,1078,1705,1729]" captionStart="Figs 82–99" captionStartId="53.[151,191,2018,2040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,232,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-116@53.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figs 82–99: Abdomen of Zyras spp.: pindarae (82–85), perforatus (86), championi (87), pallipes (88), longilobatus (89), hastatus (90), truncatus (91), latilobatus (92), morvani (93), condignus (94), hirtus (95), gardneri (96), hirsutiventris (97), parageminus (98), alternans (99). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742383/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">87</figureCitation>
): head and pronotum black; elytra reddish-yellow, with the postero-lateral portions sharply black; abdomen distinctly bicoloured: tergites II black, III–IV pale-reddish, V black with the anterior margin and the antero-lateral portions pale-reddish, VI black with the antero-lateral portions reddish, and VII–X pale-reddish; legs yellow; antennae blackishbrown to blackish, with (the apical half of) antennomere XI slightly paler; maxillary palpi yellowish to yellowishbrown with palpomere III weakly infuscate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCCE53C533F80E16236FDD5" blockId="13.[794,1399,1641,2081]" lastBlockId="14.[189,795,233,1441]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">
Head (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCCE53F537880E160ACF7B5" box="[861,935,2025,2049]" captionStart="Figs 42–54" captionStartId="46.[189,229,2012,2034]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,232,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-109@46.[189,1436,232,1971]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figs 42–54: Forebody of Zyras spp.: kraatzi (42), exasperatus (43), pindarae (44), perforatus (45), championi (46), pallipes (47), condignus, holotype (48), condignus, Nepal (49), nigroaeneus (50), morvani (51), truncatus (52), longilobatus (53), hastatus (54). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742371/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="130">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, median portion extensively impunctate; punctures in lateral portions sparse and rather fine. Eyes longer than postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCFE53C514D860162AFFE95" box="[360,420,265,289]" captionStart="Figs 1–41" captionStartId="45.[151,191,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[152,1389,232,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-203@45.[151,1398,232,1874]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Figs 1–41:Antennae of Zyrasspp.:kraatzi(1),exasperatus(2),pindarae (3–5),perforatus(6),championi(7),pallipes (8),condignus (9), nitens (10), truncatus (11), nilgiriensis (12), hirsutiventris (13), russiceps (14), brignolii (15), hastatus (16), parageminus (17–18), latilobatus (19), alternans (20), hirtus (21), nigroaeneus (22), luteipes (23), longilobatus (24), morvani (25), gratellus (Malaysia) (26), castaneus, lectotype (27),proximus (28–29),novinversus (30–31), brevilobatus(32), parvicollis(33), ambulans (34),matangensis (35), densissimus (36), densihirtus (37), nigrihirtus (38), gratellus (Sulawesi) (39), gardneri (40), titan (41). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742367/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CF69B49FFCFE53C51938601610CFE95" box="[438,519,265,289]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="131" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
long and rather massive; antennomeres IV–V weakly oblong or as long as broad, VI–X increasingly transverse and of gradually increasing width, X approximately 1.5 times as broad as long, and XI approximately as long as the combined length of IX and X. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCFE53C511D86A16288FE75" box="[312,387,425,449]" captionStart="Figs 42–54" captionStartId="46.[189,229,2012,2034]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,232,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-109@46.[189,1436,232,1971]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figs 42–54: Forebody of Zyras spp.: kraatzi (42), exasperatus (43), pindarae (44), perforatus (45), championi (46), pallipes (47), condignus, holotype (48), condignus, Nepal (49), nigroaeneus (50), morvani (51), truncatus (52), longilobatus (53), hastatus (54). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742371/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.15 times as broad as long and approximately 1.3 times as broad as head, broadest in anterior half; punctation rather fine, sparse, and very irregularly distributed, with rather large impunctate areas on either side of midline; midline broadly impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCFE53C50988561626AFCF5" blockId="14.[189,795,233,1441]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCFE53C512F8561625EFD35" box="[266,341,617,641]" captionStart="Figs 42–54" captionStartId="46.[189,229,2012,2034]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,232,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-109@46.[189,1436,232,1971]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figs 42–54: Forebody of Zyras spp.: kraatzi (42), exasperatus (43), pindarae (44), perforatus (45), championi (46), pallipes (47), condignus, holotype (48), condignus, Nepal (49), nigroaeneus (50), morvani (51), truncatus (52), longilobatus (53), hastatus (54). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742371/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) approximately 0.8 times as long as pronotum; punctation moderately coarse, defined, and very irregularly distributed, rather dense anteriorly and near scutellum, less dense laterally, and very sparse or absent in postero-median portion. Hind wings fully developed. Metatarsomere I approximately as long as the combined length of II–IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCFE53C50988441619FFA35" blockId="14.[189,795,233,1441]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCFE53C516484416287FCD5" box="[321,396,841,865]" captionStart="Figs 82–99" captionStartId="53.[151,191,2018,2040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,232,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-116@53.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figs 82–99: Abdomen of Zyras spp.: pindarae (82–85), perforatus (86), championi (87), pallipes (88), longilobatus (89), hastatus (90), truncatus (91), latilobatus (92), morvani (93), condignus (94), hirtus (95), gardneri (96), hirsutiventris (97), parageminus (98), alternans (99). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742383/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
) nearly as broad as elytra, with moderately deep anterior impressions on tergites III–V; anterior impressions of tergites III–V each with a transverse row of not very dense and mostly weakly defined non-setiferous punctures; tergites III–IV with a lateral setiferous puncture on either side and with four setiferous punctures at posterior margin; tergite V with a lateral setiferous puncture on either side and with six setiferous punctures at posterior margin; tergite VI with a transverse row of non-setiferous punctures anteriorly, with a lateral setiferous puncture on either side, and with six setiferous punctures at posterior margin; tergite VII with a narrow transverse band of non-setiferous punctures anteriorly and with two transverse rows of setiferous punctures in posterior half, posterior margin with palisade fringe; tergite VIII with setiferous punctures only in posterior portion, posterior margin convex and with indistinct concavity in the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCFE53C509882826240FA15" blockId="14.[189,795,233,1441]" box="[189,331,1417,1441]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">♂: unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCFE53C509882C161E4F995" blockId="14.[189,794,1481,1569]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCFE53C509882C16285FA55" bold="true" box="[189,398,1481,1505]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: This species is readily distinguished from all other Himalayan representatives of similar size by the conspicuous coloration of the abdomen alone.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3146527FFCFE53C5098814161B5F935" pageId="14" pageNumber="131" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFCFE53C5098814161B5F935" blockId="14.[189,794,1609,1665]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFCFE53C50988141624DF9D5" bold="true" box="[189,326,1609,1633]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Distribution</emphasis>
: The known distribution is confined to two localities in 
<collectingRegion id="49CAF84EFFCFE53C5118816262D8F935" box="[317,467,1641,1665]" country="India" name="Uttar Pradesh" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Uttar Pradesh</collectingRegion>
, North 
<collectingCountry id="F319763CFFCFE53C520181616157F935" box="[548,604,1641,1665]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">India</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFCFE53C524C816161A5F935" box="[617,686,1641,1665]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="64.[189,234,822,843]" captionTargetBox="[189,1436,232,813]" captionTargetId="figure-76@64.[189,1436,232,813]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Map 1: Revised distributions of Zyras kraatzi (black and white circles; white circle: type locality), Z. exasperatus (white circle), Z. iniquus (triangles), Z. pallipes (diamonds), and Z. championi (white stars) in the Himalaya." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742393/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Map 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
